Two YMCA employees from New South Wales (NSW) were charged with child sex offenses before the 2011 charges against Caringbah child caregiver Jonathan Lord were heard by the Royal Commission on Child Sexual Abuse.
However, in the opening statement to the commission, the YMCA had stated that "there has never been an incident of child sexual abuse in the organization."
